      </div>
      <div class="card scroll-reveal">
        <div style="font-size:2rem;">🐘</div>
        <h3>David Sheldrick Elephant Orphanage</h3>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> 2,000 KES (~€15). <strong>Open:</strong> 11am–12pm daily. Booking required. Watch baby elephants being fed. One of Nairobi's most heart‑warming experiences. <strong>Book weeks in advance.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="card scroll-reveal">
        <div style="font-size:2rem;">🦁</div>
        <h3>Nairobi National Park</h3>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $43 park fee + vehicle ($30). Best early morning (6–9am) or late afternoon (4–6pm). See lions, rhinos, giraffes with city skyline backdrop. Half‑day safari is enough.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card scroll-reveal">
        <div style="font-size:2rem;">🏛️</div>
        <h3>Karen Blixen Museum</h3>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> 1,200 KES (~€9). Explore the colonial‑era home of the "Out of Africa" author. Beautiful gardens and views of Ngong Hills.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card scroll-reveal">
        <div style="font-size:2rem;">🌿</div>
        <h3>Karura Forest</h3>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> 600 KES (~€5). 30km of walking/biking trails, waterfalls, caves. Safe and serene – a favourite among expats and locals.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card scroll-reveal">
        <div style="font-size:2rem;">🛍️</div>
        <h3>Maasai Market</h3>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free entry. Bargaining essential. Best days: Tuesday (CBD) and Saturday (KICC roof). Beads, art, fabrics, souvenirs.</p>
      </div>
